'agpeya.psalm_143.text': 'Lord, hear my prayer, attend to my supplication! not answer me in your truth, in your righteousness! <br> go into judgment with thy servant; For in thy sight no man living is righteous. <br> For the enemy pursues my soul, takes down my life, let me live in darkness like the dead of prehistoric times. <br> My mind exhausted in me, my heart is frozen in my interior. <br> I remember the days of old, consider all your doing. I meditate on the works of your hands. <br> to you I spread out my hands. Like a parched land my soul yearns for you! // <br> Quick, answer me, O Lord! It languishes my mind. Hide thy face from me! Otherwise I am like those who go down to the pit. <br> Let me hear in the morning thy mercy, because I trust in you! Tu me the path that I should go, for to you I lift up my soul <br> Save me, O Lord, from my enemies! I recall to you my refuge. <br> Teach me to do to do your will, for you are my God! Your good Spirit lead me into level land! <br> sake of your name, O Lord, give me life! In your justice lead my soul out of trouble! <br> in your grace destroy my enemies, and all enemies perish let my soul, for I am your servant! <B> Hallelujah! </ B>',
